Three and a half thousand miles away in New York, Princess Eugenie could be forgiven for thinking that her 25th birthday might pass unnoticed in the UK.

But the Queen’s granddaughter wasn’t reckoning on her father, Prince Andrew, who was determined, literally, to trumpet it from the roof tops.

In the middle of a Palace function, Andrew whipped out his iPad and used it to video call his daughter, who currently lives in Manhattan.

